{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make it compulsory for food manufacturers to list all Legumes as an allergen.",
        "additional_details": "I believe people with a legume allergy should be able to look at the list of ingredients on food packaging and be able to EASILY see if the product contains something which may cause them to have a severe allergic reaction. \r\n\r\nManufacturers should not be able to change the name of ingredients. \r\n\r\nLegumes include some of the following;\r\n\r\nLentils\r\nChickpeas \r\nGreen Peas\r\nPinto Beans\r\nMange-Tout\r\nTamarind \r\nButter Beans\r\n\r\nAnd many more.....",
        "background": "I want legumes to be listed on food packaging as an allergen. Very often legumes are used and are called something else. For example 'Gram Flour' is in fact Chickpeas. Manufacturers need to be more transparent. A legume allergy can be just as life threatening as a peanut allergy.",
